The paper deals with transactional systems, concurrency, and data structures, which are all topics that fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses garbage collection, which is a topic that falls under the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. The use of functional data structures and algorithms for acquiring, updating, and releasing versions suggests that the paper could also be classified under Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the experimental validation and comparison with state-of-the-art concurrent data structures suggest that the paper could also be classified under Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
